product_name: NYX Professional MakeupEpic Ink Waterproof Liquid Eyeliner
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganGive BackDiscover NYX Professional Makeup's #1 Epic Ink Eyeliner in 4 nude shades. 24HR wear, flake resistant, matte finish, waterproof. Go nude with confidence!
details: DetailsBenefitsGoing nude never better in the #1 Eyeliner from NYX Professional Makeup, now in 4 nude shadesNEW shades, same precision with NYX's flexible brush tip for intense pigments and epic nude liner looks24HR wear. Waterproof. Flake-resistant. Matte finishAll NYX Professional Makeup products are proudly cruelty-free and PETA certifiedFeaturing a vegan formula with no animal-derived ingredients or by-productItem 2501971How To UseUse the slender point of the felt-tip liquid eyeliner to trace along your upper lash line for subtle definition. Or, press down a touch more on the eyeliner pen to create a thicker line, then flick it upward at the outer corner of your eye for a striking cat-eye look.IngredientsAqua/Water, Butylene Glycol, Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer, Acrylates Copolymer, Alcohol, Beheneth-30, Silica, Ppg-2-Deceth-30, Peg-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Sodium Laureth Sulfate, Sodium Lauryl Sulfate, Sodium Polyaspartate, Ammonium Acrylates Copolymer, Disodium Laureth Sulfosuccinate, Caprylyl Glycol, Laureth-21, Ethylhexylglycerin, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Phenoxyethanol, Citric Acid. May Contain: Black 2 (CI 77266) [Nano], Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492).
how_to_use: Use the slender point of the felt-tip liquid eyeliner to trace along your upper lash line for subtle definition. Or, press down a touch more on the eyeliner pen to create a thicker line, then flick it upward at the outer corner of your eye for a striking cat-eye look.

reviews.headline: Not as pigmented as I would like.
reviews.comments: It's a very soft color. Not very pigmented at all, more like a light taupe color. Complimentary but you wouldn't really be able to make a noticeable line. It looks more like a line of eyeshadow with your makeup.

reviews.headline: BEST Liquid Liner I've Used
reviews.comments: I have tried EVERY expensive high end product they have out there and for me, this is hands down the best smudgeproof and sweat resistant liner I've used. I love the precise tip and it lasts a long time. Also has a great price point!!!

reviews.headline: Not a very strong pigment
reviews.comments: Honestly, I love this product on black, but the brown ink doesn't paint as strong as I would like, it looks like blurred for me so it's a little bit disappointed.

reviews.headline: No
reviews.comments: You get what you pay for, smudges, doesn't last long

I don't usually write reviews, but I had to on this. I use this eyeliner and milk, chocolate as a tight liner. This eyeliner lasts even through tears. Not only is it budge proof, but it is also smear proof.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I tried a new color, this one, and I love how it looks on me!

reviews.headline: Favorite liner!
reviews.comments: This has been the only eyeliner I've used for the past 4 years. I love it! Lasts long, pigmented, quick drying, and super precise! Unfortunately though, it is prone to leaks. I have also noticed that in the past year, I have had to buy replacements due to leakage as well as the product drying out more frequently than I have had to in previous years. Did the formula change? While this is inconvenient and frustrating, it's not enough to make me look for a different eyeliner. I will always go for my Epic Ink!

reviews.headline: Already repurchased
reviews.comments: Affordable, super wet, and lasts all day. All the prestige versions of this product have been a let down and dry out quickly. I've only been using mine for about a week, but it's always as wet as the day I opened it and have used it EVERY DAY since buying it. And bought another (Milk chocolate, then graham cracker). I absolutely love the browns!

reviews.headline: formula change
reviews.comments: i have been using this eyeliner for years but all the recent liners ive bought dry out super fast and do not last as long on my eyes. i would only have to buy every 5 months but now it feels like i have to buy a new one every month. its very disappointing, i think i need to find a new go to waterproof liner.

reviews.headline: Fabulous budget eyeliner choice!
reviews.comments: I purchased this eyeliner for the belt tip. I typically use only high-end make up and I found this budget choice in an awesome color. I'm so glad that I tried it! It glides on smoothly and last all day. I highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Formula change? bring back the old formula!
reviews.comments: I have been using this eyeliner since I was 14 years old and I am now almost 30. In the last year or so of re purchasing this product I have bought four pens and they have all be extremely subpar. Either too dry, or the ink comes out so much that is bleeds in my eyes, the bristles damage after the second or third use, the formula is patchy, and the fact that is absoloutely stings/burns my eyes is the biggest indicator of a forumla change. That has never happened before in the years of me purchasing this product. I have no idea what they have changed but PLEASE bring the old formula back. After purchasing four pens in a row (because I thought I had just got a defective pen each time) I will not be purchasing anymore. Such a shame because I have been using this for so long.

reviews.headline: Amazing color . Great staying power, but the leaks!
reviews.comments: This packaging truly ruins such an amazing product. You can store it/hold it right side up and it still drips EVERYWHERE. If you manage to not get it on your face however, it is one of the if not the best liner out

reviews.headline: Favorite
reviews.comments: Idk how this eyeliner doesn't have a 5 star rating overall. It's the only one I trust to stay on, makes a great wing, and doesn't dry out

reviews.headline: Great liner, especially for the price
reviews.comments: I love this liner. I stock up on it quite often. It's precise, long lasting, and doesn't run. Definitely happy with my purchase.

reviews.headline: Bring back the old formula!
reviews.comments: I've been buying this eyeliner since I was 13, I am 19 now. This was the best eyeliner up until about 6 months ago where they changed the formula. I've bought about 3 different liners in the span of 6 months now hoping that it was just a bad batch. The pigmented black that didn't run with a tip that didn't fray that I once knew is gone. Now the applications are incosistent, with a watery formula. It lacks pigment. I'm hoping NYX brings back the old formua I loved, but for now I'm done trying.

reviews.headline: Very picky about my eyeliner
reviews.comments: I threw this in my cart to qualify for a discount, and let me tell you ill never buy another brand eyeliner again. Glides on smooth, perfect wing every time.

reviews.headline: I will definitely purchase this eyeliner again.
reviews.comments: I have oily skin. Most eyeliners get runny right away. This one last longer.

reviews.headline: Great
reviews.comments:
I received this product for free product in exchange for my honest review Epic Ink is a high performing eyeliner that delivers sharp, matte lines with impressive staying power. For the price, it's a steal! However, it's not without its quirks, occasional leaks and drying issues can be frustrating.

If you're a detail oriented makeup enthusiast who doesn't mind a little troubleshooting, Epic Ink is a great choice. But if you prioritize hassle free application and consistency, you might want to look elsewhere.

reviews.headline: Freckles
reviews.comments: Graham cracker is great for fake freckles. Did fail a smudge test, but thats not so bad if you want lighter "freckles".

reviews.headline: changed the formula
reviews.comments: been getting this eyeliner for a couple years now and noticed after the last time I purchased, they changed the formula! :(. NYX please change it back it was so good before

media.headline: Loved it
media.caption: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I recently tried NYX's blue eyeliner as a new makeup find, and I have to say, I'm thoroughly impressed! The rich blue hue is vibrant without being overpowering, making it a fun yet wearable choice for both day and night looks.  The formula glides on smoothly, delivering a bold, defined line that stays put all day long. I especially appreciated its smudge-proof qualityonce it was set, it kept its shape through hours of wear, even on busy days. The pigment is highly concentrated, so a little goes a long way, ensuring you can achieve either a subtle or dramatic look depending on your mood.  This blue eyeliner has quickly become a favorite in my makeup routine. Whether you're looking to add a pop of color or experiment with a new trend, NYX's blue eyeliner is definitely a standout product that brings a refreshing twist to classic eyeliner looks.

faceoff_positive.comments: Love love LOVE this eyeliner! Super pigmented and easy to use ! Reminds me of Kat Von D Tatoo liner except more affordable and in my opinion a little better!
faceoff_positive.headline: Favorite Eyeliner!!

faceoff_negative.comments: I normally use Kat Von D Ink Liner, but I was out and low on money, so I bought this. It's a good product and stays on a long time, and does create great, precise lines. However, if you've got a shaky hand or are inexperienced with eyeliner, I probably wouldn't recommend it. It's super liquidy, and can easily get in your eye, and if you're not super careful, it can kind of get everywhere. It does this weird thing where it kind of flicks off my eyelashes and gets all over my face. If you're a makeup person and know how to use liquid liner, I'd recommend this, but if you're inexperienced, I'd try something else.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not bad! A little liquidy...
